# Arrays whose extent is not written in the specification.
#
# `T[]` says the size comes from the trace. It is fixed for a whole run, so
# nothing downstream ever sees an unsized type: the LLVM type is a plain array,
# .rdb rows stay fixed-size, and quantifiers still expand while the AST is
# built. Only the direction of one data flow reverses -- normally the
# specification determines the columns, and here the columns determine the
# extent.
#
# This file is run against two traces of different sizes, and must hold for
# both, which is the whole point of leaving the extent out.

data    v : integer[];
data    g : integer[][];

# The extent is addressable, which is what makes a requirement able to talk
# about a size it did not write down.
v.count > 0;
g.count > 0;
g[0].count == 2;

# Quantifiers range over however many elements the trace turned out to have.
all x in v: x > 0;
some x in v: x == 1;
all row in g: all p in row: p > 0;
all _, i in v: i < v.count;

# The first element is always 1 in both traces; the last is v.count.
v[0] == 1;
